	<description>
	<overview>Use the <b>mobileSetSoundChannelVolume</b> command to control the volume of the given channel.</overview>

		<parameters>
  <parameter>
    <name>channel</name>
    <description>The name of the channel.</description>
  </parameter>
  <parameter>
    <name>volume</name>
    <description>An integer between 1 and 100 where 0 is no volume and 100 is full volume.</description>
  </parameter>		</parameters>

	<value></value>
	<comments>Changing the volume of a channel affects the currently playing sound and any sounds played subsequently on the channel.<p></p><p>Setting the volume of a non-existent channel results in it being created. This allows the volume to be set before any sounds are played.</p></comments>
	</description>
